Just make sure you can troubleshoot and repair things without too much trouble.

If you are tightly bundling the wires, make sure all of those points are accessible without removing anything so you can add or remove wires easily.

Do not mix power wires and signal wires in the same bundle.

R613: “The PDP/PDH, associated wiring, and all circuit breakers must be visible for inspection.”

R624 allows specific, different wire colors for both positive and negative. This makes tracing wires in a bundle much easier, but in 16 seasons I haven’t seen any but black and red.
